{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17539081","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17539081"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:36:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:36:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16429"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16429","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16429"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.72,0.12,0.04,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9120"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"89985"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9120","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9120"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16429"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74144"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1286"},{"type":"tags","id":"2843"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"6166"},{"type":"tags","id":"8998"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11635"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21670"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30657"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43635"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"89985","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/89985"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of progressive pain and swelling at the base of her right thumb. She works as a massage therapist and has noticed the pain is particularly severe after work. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is tenderness and mild swelling over the radial styloid process. Pain is reproduced when the thumb is flexed across the palm and the wrist is moved into ulnar deviation. There is no erythema or warmth. The remainder of the hand and wrist examination is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Osteoarthritis of the first carpometacarpal joint","De Quervain tenosynovitis","Flexor carpi radialis tendinitis","Carpal tunnel syndrome","Extensor pollicis longus tendinitis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of De Quervain tenosynovitis, which is inflammation of the first dorsal compartment of the wrist containing the abductor pollicis longus and extensor pollicis brevis tendons. The condition typically affects people who perform repetitive movements involving the thumb and wrist, such as massage therapists, new parents holding babies, or people who frequently use smartphones.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDe Quervain tenosynovitis\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by pain and tenderness over the radial styloid process, which is exacerbated by thumb and wrist movements. The positive Finkelstein test (pain on ulnar deviation of the wrist with the thumb flexed across the palm) is highly specific for this condition. Initial treatment involves activity modification, thumb spica splinting, and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs. If conservative measures fail after 4-6 weeks, corticosteroid injection into the tendon sheath is highly effective. Surgery is reserved for cases that fail to respond to conservative treatment and injections.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarpal tunnel syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with numbness and tingling in the median nerve distribution (thumb, index, middle fingers and radial half of the ring finger), often worse at night. It would not cause localised tenderness over the radial styloid.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoarthritis of the first carpometacarpal joint\u003C/strong\u003E would present with pain at the base of the thumb, but would show degenerative changes on examination including crepitus, reduced range of motion, and pain with compression. It typically affects older patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensor pollicis longus tendinitis\u003C/strong\u003E causes pain along the dorsal aspect of the thumb and wrist, particularly with thumb extension. The location would be more dorsal than in this case and Finkelstein test would not typically reproduce the pain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexor carpi radialis tendinitis\u003C/strong\u003E causes pain and tenderness along the course of the flexor carpi radialis tendon on the volar aspect of the wrist, particularly with wrist flexion and radial deviation. The location and provocative movements would differ from this case.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["De Quervain tenosynovitis typically presents with pain and tenderness over the radial styloid process, exacerbated by thumb and wrist movements.","Finkelstein test is a specific clinical test for diagnosing De Quervain tenosynovitis.","Initial treatment of De Quervain tenosynovitis includes activity modification, splinting, and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs."],"references":["Fakoya AO, Tarzian M, Sabater EL, Burgos DM, Maldonado Marty GI. De Quervain\u2019s Disease: A Discourse on Etiology, Diagnosis, and Treatment. Cureus [Internet]. 2023 Apr 24;15(4). Available at: https://assets.cureus.com/uploads/review_article/pdf/149599/20230525-24113-1r6ssap.pdf","\u200cAllbrook V. \u0027The side of my wrist hurts\u0027: De Quervain\u0027s tenosynovitis. Aust J Gen Pract. 2019 Nov;48(11):753-756. doi: 10.31128/AJGP-07-19-5018. PMID: 31722458. [cited 2025 Mar 11] Available at: https://www1.racgp.org.au/ajgp/2019/november/side-of-my-wrist-hurts"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74144"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16429"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74144","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/74144"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-11T15:05:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-11T15:05:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9120"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"89985"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"27","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/27"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc77","name":"Occupational/Environmental Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","i